Buy yourself new locks.<br>
They come in all types, dead bolt, whatever you want (door knobs included). Get a screwdriver and in 10 minutes there you go, a secure house, which is the most important thing, especially with a 15 year old sister at home... not issues with the land lord. Those can be settled later, after your home is secure.<br>
<br>
Give the old locks, and the receipt for the new locks, to your land lord, with your next rent check for minus the cost.<br>
<br>
Locks run about $10 - $20 bucks.<br>
A 10 year old can install them, it's a no brainer.<br>
Two screws, that's all. Follow the directions, you can't mess it up.<br>
<br>
Seriously, just fix it yourself, F the stupid land lord, having locks is more important right now. I change locks any time I move, when I move out, I put the old locks back on.<br>
You can do that as well, and keep your new locks to swap out at the next place you live.<br>
Some fights aren't worth fighting, and from my experience, that is one of them. Especially (and this is most important) if you do not have renter's insurance.<br>
<br>
Someone breaks in, all your stuff is gone, and you are S.O.L.<br>
Not to mention your little sister's and mom's safety! Of course.<br>
<br>
I expect you to be on your way to the local hardware store as soon as you finish reading this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.saraquael.com">
