<br>
I'm no woodsmith and I wont pretend I have any idea on what could have caused this, but I dont really know how to fix it or realign it.  If I did, I'd just do it myself.<br>
<br>
I didnt give written notice for this because, as I said, I just like to go easy with it.  I presumed that since I made it aware too them that it needed fixed, that it would be.  After this much time, then the theft of my car, I've become rather annoyed since its obvious thieves wander around my area.<br>
<br>
I'm not out to make a suit or anything.  I just wanted information so when I go in to get bitchy with them, I can point out things too them for exactly this kind of thing.  I'd rather go in and rant and complain with knowing what I'm talking about then just talking out my ass.  I dont try to argue cases I wont win or know anything about, in this case I knew I could bring up moral issues easily, but some people simply dont care.  Threaten legal issues, people begin to care when they might be losing money.  Hence the reason I came here too see.  I know we got some smart people here that know where to look for information if they dont already know it, so I knew I could rely upon you guys for help.  Obviously I was correct.<br>
<br>
We have already taken a look at some locksmiths in the area, too see what its going whose close by and to begin gettin a price.  Lot of things havent been going well so money is tight, so I'm more inclined into getting my renters scared I'm going to do something too them and make them fix it then hope to cover the bill myself.<br>
<br>
I'm also located in Savannah, GA.  I normally ask Lith for information, but of late I havent managed too find him, my guess being a police officer and just having 4th of July has kept him busy.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the information and suggestions.<br>
